This property defines the mapping from document type (file extension) to the image/icon that represents the document type.
Supported image types are "icon" and "image".

You can customize the icon or image by creating a new system property "glide.search.doctype_to_image_mapper.override". Below is an example:

{
   "pdf": { "imageType": "icon", "imageName": "document-outline" }
}

To use image type, upload an image to db_image table and set the image name in the configuration. For example:

{
   "pdf": { "imageType": "image", "imageName": "example-image.jpg" }
}

